  "texts": [
    "The LMCI stage (frames 3 and 4) is marked by below-average memory and moderate dementia that has minimal effect on daily activities [6].",
    "In this stage, the diseased cannot manage their daily affairs (such as coping with their profession) [5].",
    "AD's terminal stage (frames 5 and 6) is characterised by severe functional impairment that interferes with essential daily activities and necessitates frequent assistance [4,7].",
    "At this phase, the AD patient relies entirely on their caregiver, which causes significant physical and mental strain on the patient and their caretaking family members.",
    "MCI is a transitional stage from CN to dementia, with a 10% chance of progressing to AD."
  ],
